\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {II}{\ignorespaces Synthetic regime-switch task. MSE over 10 seeds; standard deviations are reported in parentheses. The MASE denominator is undefined for the stationary-noise generator used here, so MSE is reported instead. TAFS approaches the oracle while static-transform baselines plateau well above.}}{5}{table.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:synthetic}{{II}{5}{Synthetic regime-switch task. MSE over 10 seeds; standard deviations are reported in parentheses. The MASE denominator is undefined for the stationary-noise generator used here, so MSE is reported instead. TAFS approaches the oracle while static-transform baselines plateau well above}{table.2}{}}
